The status can be successfully saved
1.Open function button 2.Switch thermal mode to Quiet/balance/performance Mode 3.Open Settings-System-Power&Battery-Power mode page
1.Function successfully opened 2.Thermal mode switch successful 3.Power mode display noraml，Need to distinguish AC/DC status In quiet mode, the power mode should display 'Best power Efficiency' In balanced mode, the power mode should display 'Balanced'‘ In performance mode, the power mode should display 'Best Performance'‘.Performance mode does not support DC state switching
On the settings-system-power&battery page, modify the power mode to 'best power efficiency'/'balance'/'best performance'
The thermal mode in Legion Space will be synchronously modified to the corresponding mode. Quiet mode corresponds to best power efficiency. Balance mode corresponds to balanced . Performance mode corresponds to best performance
1.Connect to AC, 2.Switch from thermal mode to custom mode 3.Click to modify the mode of 'Associated with system power mode' to'best power efficiency'/'balance'/'best performance' A gear setting button will be added in the upper right corner of the associated with system power mode
1.Enter AC mode 2.Successfully entered custom mode 3.Successfully modified power mode to 'best power efficiency'/'balance'/'best performance' The power mode in settings-system-power&battery will be updated synchronously The power mode in settings system power&battery cannot be reverse linked to the power mode in custom mode in Legion Space
1.turn off function button 2.Open Settings-System-Power&Battery-Power mode page 3.Sitch thermal mode to Quiet/balance/performance Mode
1.Function successfully closed 2.Power mode display noraml，Need to distinguish AC/DC status 2.Thermal mode switch successfull 3.The power mode in settings-system-power&battery will not switch synchronously with the thermal mode
Unplug the power and enter DC mode
Switching between different thermal modes
The power mode in settings system power&battery will not switch synchronously with the thermal mode
Enable the function and click to switch between different thermal modes on the Legion Space thermal mode setting page
Power mode will switch with thermal mode Note:The performance mode can be clicked and linked normally. The power mode is linked to the thermal mode setting page

Section : Network Boost (60) Attachment :
Workloading : (Min) LeadingTime : (Min) Phase :
1.Prepare: Before testing this section, you should open some apps and keep in the background. 2.Testing needs to cover both wired and wireless networks
Operation completed
Check the‘Network Boost’ Function
Page display is complete without garbled code, interface error and leakage, key missing, key can not be clicked and other problems Function default set to off state
Set the status of Network Boost to on
Network Boost toggle status is on
Click the gear icon
Network Boost subpage is opened
Click ‘+’ button to open the windows 'Add' and select some process (like QQ,Baiduyun,QQ live)
The selected process can been added succesfully
1.Turn off 'Network Boost' button 2.Launch the App（Example：Tencent Video，BaiduYun,Youku) to test the upload/download speed
Record completed
1.Turn off 'Network Boost' button and launch a game like "CSGO2" 2.Launch the App（Example：Tencent Video，BaiduYun,Youku) to test the upload/download speed
The upload/download speed value are about same as U1/D1
Turn on 'Network Boost' button and launch a game like "CSGO2" + upload/download something from network or watching video online
The speed of downloading and uploading will be limited (The speed lower than U1/D1) "The speed of downloading and uploading" refers to the speed of other APP or watching video online, not the speed of gaming The limit is to download 1MB, which is approximately 8 Mbps, and upload 30KB, which is approximately 240Kbps.
Add the process of the upload/download apps（Example：Tencent Video，BaiduYun,Youku) or online video apps in to 'Network boost' list in Legion Space
The speed of these added downloading and uploading process will not be limited, the speed same as U1/D1.
Uninstall the added apps from system and reboot the machine
The added process could be removed from Network Boost list in Legion Space
Switch the status to ‘on/off’. Do Sleep/Hibernate/Cold boot/Warm boot operations.Restart Legion Space to check if the function has been saved.
The Function statues can be successfully saved
